==Italian==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From Latinised [[Greek]] [[forma]], an anagram of [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μόρφα]]''' (''morfa'') "bodily form, build", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μορφή]]''' (''morfe'') 
"shape, fashion, appearance,  outward form, contour, figure"

===Noun===
